Nice opaque color. Funky, wild nose cherries and maybe with a touch of licorice. Maybe. Great bitter dark chocolate flavor.

Brewed in 2006. Pours a gorgeous burnt amber color without any carbonation. Still carries the calvados aroma, but the taste is overwhelmed with sweet raisin flavor. I expected the consistency to be a little thicker, more like a rdeux, if it had this sweetness. Haha

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Nice burnt amber color with light colored carbonation. Dried fruit and caramel nose. Lightly hopped to offset the sweet caramel taste. Good finish. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Beautiful dark pour with brown head. Roasted coffee nose. Bitter chocolate and coffee taste with a creamy mouth coating.

Belgian Style Blonde brewed in Richmond, VA.  Great flagship beer.  Color: Straw unfiltered haze.  Taste reminds me of the Guillotine from Delerium maybe a fresh westmalle trippel.  Keep it up guys cant wait to taste what you do next.
Wonderful ipa.  Beautiful copper/amber color.  Delightful piney and hoppy nose.  Great bitterness.  Awesome ipa.
Bottle: nice golden color.  Beautiful sweet aroma.  Taste raisins, maltiness and maybe a hint of tropical fruit.  The abv is not overpowering.  Nice overall beer.
I jet had this beer last night.  Completely took me by surprise.  Nice hoppy aroma.  Great balance of sweet and bitter.  Im looking forward to more duclaw products in the near future.
WOW!  you had me at the nose.  I just had this beer draft....and dont understand why it hasnt been in my life longer.  Sweet with complete hop balance.  Incredible

Had this wonderful abbey quad last night...draft....during the super bowl.  took beer pizza and wings to a new level...haha!  this is one of my favorites.  wonderful malty fruity aroma.  the taste is not overly sweet like many quads can be.  delicious beer...i may have to go back to get more while its still on tap.
Bottle.  aroma: hoppy, caramel, a little citrus.  beautiful cedar color.  very balanced taste.  easy to drink.  sweet and bitter.  more malt than hops.  leave a lightly bitter after-taste.
Great malty..roasty aroma...raisins.  Beautiful dark brown, red color.  Emperors crand cru...mmmm.  Ill add more later...
beer_name: Gouden Carolus Cuvee Van De Keizer Blauw/Blue

review_blob: First, this beer caught me completely off-guard.  The nose was not up my alley.  The color, a little litght.  Well...upon tasting....this beer is solid.  More wine flavors than beer.  Chardonay creaminess......riesling sweetness.  Nice beer...I love estate beers.

Im currently drinking a draft urthel 12...its a little too cold so Im not picking up on all of the nuances of the aroma....sure I know I could wait and let it naturally warm up to room temp, but I cant.  The taste is wonderful.  I admit...Im a abt/quad head.  Great balance.  Sweet...malty.  Leaves a little bitter tinniness on the finish.  Nice quad.
Nice ipa.  Very balanced taste.  leaves a bit of a bitter after-taste.  Great hoppy aroma.

Bernardus 6 is a wonderful dubbel.  Nice aroma.  Im currently drinking a draft "6.". Wonderfully balanced with a great nose.  I cant wait to have one fresh in Belgium in march when im attending the zythos 2011.
Great imperial ipa.  nice honey notes.  great hoppy aroma.  superbly balanced...great finish.  no bitterness.  i wish it was just a little less sweet.
Perfect Stout.  Opaque.  mmmm  coffee stouts can be offered overpowered by the coffee.  Yeti can handle the espresso roast and end up completely balanced.
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Espresso Oak Aged

review_blob: Gateway.  sweet trappist malt.  Perfection!!!!!  Everytime I see this in the store i cant help but buy one.
This beer has an incredible color...devil dancer should be a color in a box of crayons.  The nose is amazing...WOW!  Please keep making this beer.
